# Homebrige on Docker

The easiest way to start your Homebridge ensuring Docker Compose is installed.

# Setup

Clone the repository:

```sh
git clone https://github.com/alex2io/homebrige-docker.git
```

Change the directory:

```sh
cd homebrige-docker
```

Run the following command to start the Homebridge Docker container:

```sh
docker-compose up -d
```

Visit http://localhost:8581
